CAPE TOWN - Parliament on Wednesday threatened to subpoena former Steinhoff CEO Markus Jooste and former chief financial officer Ben la Grange if they fail to appear before MPs within 10 days. Parliament has decided to give former #Steinhoff CFO Ben la Grange and Former CEO Markus Jooste 10 days to appear before Committee or face subpoena. MPs are being updates on the Steinhoff investigations on Wednesday, with the Hawks, the JSE and the Financial Services Board expected to make presentations. On Tuesday, Parliament released a letter from former Steinhoff boss Markus Jooste’s lawyers, informing them that Jooste would not be attending Wednesday’s proceedings. READ: Parliament committees to decide whether to subpoena Markus Jooste According to the letter, appearing before the committees would undermine Jooste's right to a fair trial. Jooste is under criminal investigation by the Hawks. Former #Steinhoff CFO Ben La Grange also declining to attend Parliaments committee today.... Markus Jooste flat out refusing is likely to be subpoenaed today. @eNCA pic.twitter.com/XSsk61IxUz The Financial Services Board is conducting 4 investigations on #Steinhoff : insider Trading and False Statements. German and Dutch investigative teams. @eNCA pic.twitter.com/etE6zx4idI eNCA